<subSubSection pageId="161" pageNumber="162" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="161" pageNumber="162">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="161" pageNumber="162">
Variable woody based perennial with thick woody taproot, sometimes cushion-forming, with several ascending stems in a loose tuft to c. 20 cm in height, stems and all vegetative parts with long spreading hairs. Basal leaves 4-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.8 cm, oblong or oblanceolate, acute, entire, narrowed to a long petiole-like base; stem leaves sessile, 3-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.6-0.9 cm, oblong-elliptic, acute, entire, cuneate at the base. Flowers in many-flowered terminal heads, occasionally also 1-2 flowers in the axil of the uppermost leaf; bracts 1.3-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-0.6 cm, linear-oblong or lanceolate, acute, pilose; bracteoles 11-16 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1 mm, linear, pilose; pedicels 0-3 mm; outer sepals 6-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2 mm, lanceolate, long acuminate, pilose; inner sepals abruptly narrowed around the middle with a caudate apex; corolla 1.5-2 cm, white or pink, not lobed, midpetaline bands pilose, darker; ovary pilose; style pilose, divided c. 3 mm above base, stigmas 3-5 mm. Capsule pilose; seeds pubescent. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
